<refsect1 id='output_formats'><title>Output Formats</title>
<para>
  Some devices allow the PCM output format to be specified as follows:
</para>
<blockquote remap='RS'>
  <variablelist remap='TP'>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<userinput>FLOAT</userinput>
      </term>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  32 bit floating point.
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</blockquote>
<blockquote remap='RS'>
  <variablelist remap='TP'>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<userinput>S16_LE</userinput>
      </term>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  16 bit integer, little endian.
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</blockquote>
<blockquote remap='RS'>
  <variablelist remap='TP'>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<userinput>S32_LE</userinput>
      </term>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  32 bit integer, little-endian.
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</blockquote>
</refsect1>

<refsect1 id='configuration'><title>Configuration</title>
<para>
  <command>glassplayer</command>
  <manvolnum>1</manvolnum> reads its startup options from one or more
  of the following locations, with values from locations
  read earlier taking precedence over those read later:
</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	command line
      </term>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<filename>$HOME/.glassplayerrc</filename>
      </term>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<filename>/etc/glassplayer.conf</filename>
      </term>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</refsect1>

